# Downstream-context allowlist for manifest-completeness.test.sh.
#
# The completeness guard requires every git-tracked file to be classified by
# docs/export-manifest.md. That manifest enumerates TEMPLATE paths — a downstream
# repo also tracks files the template knows nothing about (its own project code,
# local tooling, assets), which would otherwise fail the guard as UNCOVERED even
# with zero template drift.
#
# List those downstream-OWNED paths here to exclude them from the completeness
# sweep. One repo-relative path or glob per line; text after '#' is a comment.
# Entries may be:
#   - an exact path            app/svelte.config.js
#   - a directory prefix (/)   app/            (everything under app/)
#   - a glob (* ? [])          src/*.ts        assets/*.png
# A directory prefix or glob keeps future files under it covered automatically.
#
# Keep entries specific. An over-broad entry built only from glob metacharacters
# (`*`, `**`, `*/`, ...) would exclude ~every file and silently neuter the guard;
# such entries are REJECTED at load time with a warning, never applied.
#
# This file is DOWNSTREAM-OWNED and fail-open: absent or comment-only means no
# downstream exclusions (the template ships it with no active entries — it has no
# downstream project code of its own). It is the manifest analogue of
# tools/tests/governance-scan.allow. The vendored template snapshot itself
# (.minions-template/ and .minions-template.next/) is excluded by the guard
# built-in and does NOT need an entry here.
#
# --- downstream entries below (none in the template) ---
